  "response": "Donald Trump has expressed skepticism about the scientific consensus surrounding global warming and climate change. While he has occasionally made conflicting statements on the topic, his general stance has been one of questioning the validity and urgency of climate change. During his presidency, he rolled back several environmental regulations and withdrew the United States from the Paris Agreement, citing economic concerns and skepticism about the impact of human activities on global warming. However, as with many public figures, his statements and positions can evolve over time.",
